[SN]TITLE[SN]
Thirteen rescued form burning block of flats in Southampton

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Thirteen people were rescued from a block of flats in Southampton after a fire in a first-floor kitchen.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
A man was rescued by firefighters from the burning flat in Lydgate Road, and a woman fled the property.
Hampshire Fire and Rescue crews from Hightown and St Mary's were called to the scene at 02:30 GMT.
Three more people were rescued from the balcony of a neighbouring flat with a ladder and eight others were led outside by firefighters.
South Central Ambulance Service said a 20-year-old man was taken to Southampton General Hospital to be treated for smoke inhalation.
The cause of the fire is under investigation.
